{
  "texts": [
    "Plasmid systems were highly heterogeneous in their genetic complexity.",
    "Thirty-seven plasmid systems contained sequences that could be classified into seven different plasmid incompatibility types (Inc11, Inc18, IncFIB, IncFIC, IncI-ɣ/K1, IncK2/Z and IncW; Supplementary Table 9).",
    "Furthermore, 602 plasmid systems contained at least two non-redundant compound plasmids, with the largest system containing 168 non-redundant compound plasmids (Fig. 4c).",
    "For example, pFIJ1037_1, one of the plasmids we isolated and transferred between B. fragilis strains, was part of PS486, a system containing 24 non-redundant plasmids and found across a total of 127 metagenomes.",
    "The PS486 backbone consists of a replication protein and a toxin-antitoxin system, and the cargo genes include β-lactamases, erythromycin Analysis https://doi.org/10.1038/s41564-024-01610-3 resistance, tetracycline resistance and riboflavin biosynthesis (Fig. 4d and Supplementary Table 11)."
  ]
}